  image(images.at("4.1").path, width: 50%),
)

== Earth's Tilt and Seasonality
- The earth’s axis is tilted 23.5°, causing seasonal changes in solar radiation and climate.
- The solar equator shifts north and south, producing seasonal temperature and precipitation cycles.
- Temperature variation is greatest at high latitudes, especially in the Northern Hemisphere due to less ocean moderation.
