= Atmospheric Circulation
== Water Vapor and Precipitation
- Water vapor pressure increases with temperature; warm air holds more moisture.
- Precipitation occurs when air cools and water vapor condenses, controlled by equilibrium vapor pressure.
#figure(
  image(images.at("4.4").path, width: 50%),
)

== Hadley, Ferrel, and Polar Cells
- Hadley cells: Warm air rises at the equator, cools, and sinks at 30° latitude, creating tropical rainforests and deserts.
- Ferrel cells: Circulate air in temperate zones, driven by Hadley cells.
- Polar cells: Circulate cold air at high latitudes.
- The Coriolis effect causes winds to curve, forming trade winds and westerlies.
